'''土壤侵蝕'''是[[土壤退化|土壤退化]]的一種形式。 [[土地|土地]]的[[侵蝕|侵蝕]]是在所有土地上自然發生的過程。土壤侵蝕的因素是水和風，每年造成大量的土壤流失。土壤侵蝕可能是一個緩慢的過程，持續相對未被注意到，或者它可能以驚人的速率發生，導致表土嚴重損失。農田土壤的損失可能反映在減少作物生產潛力，降低地表水質和破壞排水網絡。

雖然侵蝕是一個自然過程，但人類活動卻增加了全球侵蝕發生率的10至40倍。過度（或加速）侵蝕導致'''現場'''和'''非現場'''問題。現場影響包括由於營養豐富的上層[[土層|土層]]的損失，[[農業生產力|農業生產力]]、[[自然景觀|自然景觀]]和[[生態崩潰|生態崩潰]]在某些情況下，最終的結果是[[荒漠化|荒漠化]]。場外影響包括河流的侵蝕、農業泥沙輸送和水體富營養化、以及與道路和房屋相關的沉積物相關的損害。水和風蝕是[[土地退化|土地退化]]的兩個主要原因；結合起來，他們負責全球退化土地面積的約84％，使過度侵蝕成為世界上最重要的[[環境問題|環境問題]]。<ref name="Springer">{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Soil and water conservation|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|page=2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA2|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085328/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA2|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="toy-2002-p1" />[[毀林|毀林]]、[[道路|道路]]、人為[[氣候變化|氣候變化]]和[[城市擴張|城市擴張]]是其對人類活動侵蝕。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Julien, Pierre Y.|title=Erosion and Sedimentation|publisher=Cambridge University. (Press|year=2010|isbn=978-0-521-53737-7|page=1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Gv72uiVmWEYC&pg=PA1|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801101120/https://books.google.com/books?id=Gv72uiVmWEYC&pg=PA1|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而，有許多可以減少或限制脆弱土壤侵蝕的預防和補救做法。

== 物理過程 ==

=== 降雨和地表徑流 ===
[[File:Rummu_aherainemägi2.jpg|thumb]]，降雨造成的侵蝕過程]]

[[降雨|降雨]]和可能由降雨產生的[[地表徑流|地表徑流]]產生四種主要類型的水土流失：'''飛濺侵蝕'''、'''板材侵蝕'''、'''侵蝕'''、'''溝蝕'''。濺水侵蝕通常被認為是土壤侵蝕過程中的第一和最不嚴重的階段，其後是板材侵蝕，然後是侵蝕，最後是溝槽侵蝕（四個中最嚴重的）。<ref>{{cite book|author=Toy, Terrence J.|title=Soil Erosion: Processes, Prediction, Measurement, and Control|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2002|isbn=978-0-471-38369-7|pages=60–61|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7YBaKZ-28j0C&pg=PA60|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609080042/https://books.google.com/books?id=7YBaKZ-28j0C&pg=PA60|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Zachar, Dušan|chapter=Classification of soil erosion|title=Soil Erosion|volume=Vol. 10|publisher=Elsevier|year=1982|isbn=978-0-444-99725-8|page=48|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o8ny2dUkpM8C&pg=PA48|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801093326/https://books.google.com/books?id=o8ny2dUkpM8C&pg=PA48|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在'''飛濺侵蝕'''中，[[降雨|降雨]]在土壤中會產生一個小火山口，<ref name="Fig. 4">See figure 4 in {{cite journal|last1=Obreschkow|title=Confined Shocks inside Isolated Liquid Volumes – A New Path of Erosion?|year=2011|arxiv=1109.3175 |journal=Physics of Fluids}}</ref> 噴射土壤顆粒。<ref>Cheraghi, M., S. Jomaa, G. C. Sander, and D. A. Barry (2016 ), Hysteretic sediment ﬂuxes in rainfall-driven soil erosion: Particle size effects, Water Resour. Res., 52, doi:10.1002/2016WR019314</ref>這些土壤顆粒行進的距離在水平地面上可以高達0.6米（2英尺）垂直和1.5米（5英尺）。

如果表面徑流土壤飽和，或者如果降雨率大於水可以滲入土壤的速率，則表面徑流發生。 如果徑流具有足夠的流動能量，它會將鬆散的土壤顆粒運輸到斜坡上。<ref name="FAO-1965-pp23-25">{{cite book|author=Food and Agriculture Organization|chapter=Types of erosion damage|title=Soil Erosion by Water: Some Measures for Its Control on Cultivated Lands|publisher=United Nations|year=1965|isbn=978-92-5-100474-6|pages=23–25|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6KeL3ix6ZqQC&pg=PA23|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801123919/https://books.google.com/books?id=6KeL3ix6ZqQC&pg=PA23|dead-url=no}}</ref>'''板材侵蝕'''是通過陸上流動運輸鬆散的土壤顆粒。<ref name="FAO-1965-pp23-25" />

'''侵蝕'''指的是小的、短暫的集中的流動路徑的發展，其作為沈積物源和[[沉積物|沉積物]]遞送系統用於在山坡上侵蝕。一般來說，在[[乾旱|乾旱]][[旱地|旱地]]地區的水土流失率最大的地方，河流活動活躍。溝槽中的流動深度通常為幾厘米（約一英寸）或更小的量級，並且沿通道的斜率可能相當陡。這意味著，河流表現出[[水力|水力]]物理學與流經更深，更寬的河流和河流的水非常不同。<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Nearing | first1 = M.A. | last2 = Norton | first2 = L.D. | last3 = Bulgakov | first3 = D.A. | last4 = Larionov | first4 = G.A. | last5 = West | first5 = L.T. | last6 = Dontsova | first6 = K.M. | year = 1997 | title = Hydraulics and erosion in eroding rills | url = | journal = Water Resources Research | volume = 33 | issue = 4| pages = 865–876 | doi=10.1029/97wr00013 | bibcode=1997WRR....33..865N}}</ref>

當暴雨或融化的雪期間或之後，當徑流水積聚並在狹窄通道中迅速流動時，發生[[溝槽侵蝕|溝槽侵蝕]]，從而將土壤移除到相當深的深度。<ref>{{cite book|author=Poesen, Jean|chapter=Gully erosion in Europe|editor=Boardman, John|editor2=Poesen, Jean|title=Soil Erosion in Europe|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2007|isbn=978-0-470-85911-7|pages=516–519|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vvOFRskFunwC&pg=PA516|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609080040/https://books.google.com/books?id=vvOFRskFunwC&pg=PA516|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Poesen, Jean|chapter=Gully erosion in dryland environments|editor=Bull, Louise J.|editor2=Kirby, M.J.|title=Dryland Rivers: Hydrology and Geomorphology of Semi-Arid Channels|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2002|isbn=978-0-471-49123-1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qjHoYZXQee0C&pg=PA229|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085549/https://books.google.com/books?id=qjHoYZXQee0C&pg=PA229|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Borah, Deva K.|chapter=Watershed sediment yield|editor=Garcia, Marcelo H.|title=Sedimentation Engineering: Processes, Measurements, Modeling, and Practice|publisher=ASCE Publishing|year=2008|isbn=978-0-7844-0814-8|page=828|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1AsypwBUa_wC&pg=PA828|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085348/https://books.google.com/books?id=1AsypwBUa_wC&pg=PA828|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 河流和溪流 ===
[[File:Dobbingstone_Burn_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1291882.jpg|thumb]]

'''河流侵蝕'''發生在沿著線性特徵的連續水流的情況下。侵蝕是向下，深化山谷和源頭侵蝕，將山谷延伸到山坡，創造陡岸。在流侵蝕的最早階段，侵蝕活動主要是垂直的，谷地具有典型的'''V'''橫截面，並且流坡度相對陡峭。當達到一定程度時，侵蝕活動切換到橫向侵蝕，這擴大了谷底並產生了狹窄的漫灘。流體梯度變得接近平坦，並且沉積物的橫向沉積變得重要，因為流體流過谷底。在流侵蝕的所有階段中，到目前為止，在洪水時期發生最大的侵蝕，當更多和更快移動的水可用於攜帶更大的沉積物負荷時。在這樣的過程中，不是單獨的水侵蝕：懸浮的磨料顆粒，[[卵石|卵石]]和[[石頭|石頭]]也可以在它們穿過表面時在被稱為'''牽引'''的過程中侵蝕性地起作用。<ref>Ritter, Michael E. (2006) [http://www4.uwsp.edu/geo/faculty/ritter/geog101/textbook/fluvial_systems/geologic_work_of_streams.html "Geologic Work of Streams"] {{Wayback|url=http://www4.uwsp.edu/geo/faculty/ritter/geog101/textbook/fluvial_systems/geologic_work_of_streams.html |date=20120506040721 }} ''The Physical Environment: an Introduction to Physical Geography'' University of Wisconsin, {{OCLC|79006225}}</ref>

'''河岸侵蝕'''是河岸的磨損。 這不同於水道床上的變化，其被稱為“沖刷”。 侵蝕和河岸形式的變化可以通過將金屬桿插入堤岸並在不同時間沿著桿標記堤岸表面的位置來測量。<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_PJHw-hSKGgC&pg=PA113 |title=Stream hydrology: an introduction for ecologists |author=Nancy D. Gordon |chapter=Erosion and Scour |isbn=978-0-470-84357-4 |date=2004-06-01 |postscript= |access-date=2017-01-30 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085254/https://books.google.com/books?id=_PJHw-hSKGgC&pg=PA113 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

'''熱侵蝕'''是由於移動水而熔化和削弱[[永久凍土|永久凍土]]的結果。<ref name="nsidc_thermal">{{cite web |url=http://nsidc.org/cgi-bin/words/word.pl?thermal%20erosion |title=Thermal Erosion |work=NSIDC Glossary |publisher=[[National_Snow_and_Ice_Data_Center|National Snow and Ice Data Center]] |accessdate=21 December 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uLakeCcx?url=http://nsidc.org/cgi-bin/words/word.pl?thermal%20erosion |archivedate=2010-11-19 |deadurl=no }}</ref> 它可以發生在沿河和海岸。在西伯利亞觀察到的快速消失是由於熱侵蝕，因為河岸的這些部分由永凍土膠結的非粘性材料組成。<ref name="lena">{{cite journal|doi=10.1002/esp.592|title=Fluvial thermal erosion investigations along a rapidly eroding river bank: application to the Lena River (central Siberia)|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_earth-surface-processes-and-landforms_2003-11_28_12/page/1349|year=2003|last1=Costard|first1=F.|last2=Dupeyrat|first2=L.|last3=Gautier|first3=E.|last4=Carey-Gailhardis|first4=E.|journal=Earth Surface Processes and Landforms|volume=28|pages=1349–1359|bibcode = 2003ESPL...28.1349C|issue=12 }}</ref> 

Much of this erosion occurs as the weakened banks fail in large slumps. Thermal erosion also affects the [[Arctic|Arctic]] coast, where wave action and near-shore temperatures combine to undercut permafrost bluffs along the shoreline and cause them to fail. Annual erosion rates along a {{convert|100|km|mi|abbr=off|adj=on}} segment of the Beaufort Sea shoreline averaged {{convert|5.6|m|ft|abbr=off}} per year from 1955 to 2002.<ref name="jones_arctic">{{cite journal |last=Jones |first=B.M. |author2=Hinkel, K.M. |author3=Arp, C.D. |author4=Eisner, W.R. |year=2008 |title=Modern Erosion Rates and Loss of Coastal Features and Sites, Beaufort Sea Coastline, Alaska |journal=Arctic |publisher=[[Arctic_Institute_of_North_America|Arctic Institute of North America]] |volume=61 |issue=4 |pages=361–372 |url=http://arctic.synergiesprairies.ca/arctic/index.php/arctic/article/view/44/115 |doi=10.14430/arctic44 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517101602/http://arctic.synergiesprairies.ca/arctic/index.php/arctic/article/view/44/115 |archivedate=2013-05-17 |access-date=2017-01-30 }}</ref>

=== 洪水 ===
在極高的流量下，[[漩渦|漩渦]]由大量快速沖刷的水形成。例子：大洪水它在[[華盛頓州|華盛頓州]][[哥倫比亞盆地|哥倫比亞盆地]]地區的沖成廣大河溝地形。<ref>See, for example: {{cite book|author=Alt, David|title=Glacial Lake Missoula & its Humongous Floods|publisher=Mountain Press|year=2001|isbn=978-0-87842-415-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s4y3c8fxeEwC|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801112819/https://books.google.com/books?id=s4y3c8fxeEwC|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 風蝕 ===
[[File:Im_Salar_de_Uyuni.jpg|thumb]]，由風蝕造成的岩層。]]
{{main article|風蝕}}
風蝕是一種主要的[[地貌|地貌]]力，特別是在[[乾旱|乾旱]]地區和[[半乾旱|半乾旱]]地區。它還是土地退化、蒸發、荒漠化，有害的空氣中粉塵和作物損害的主要來源-特別是在人類活動如[[砍伐森林|砍伐森林]]、[[城市化|城市化]]和[[農業|農業]]。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Zheng, Xiaojing|author2=Huang, Ning|last-author-amp=yes|title=Mechanics of Wind-Blown Sand Movements|publisher=Springer|year=2009|isbn=978-3-540-88253-4|pages=7–8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R6kYrbA3XSAC&pg=PA7|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801102134/https://books.google.com/books?id=R6kYrbA3XSAC&pg=PA7|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Cornelis, Wim S.|chapter=Hydroclimatology of wind erosion in arid and semi-arid environments|editor=D'Odorico, Paolo|editor2=Porporato, Amilcare|title=Dryland Ecohydrology|publisher=Springer|year=2006|isbn=978-1-4020-4261-4|page=141|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rUsUPZbFHK8C&pg=PA141|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801111412/https://books.google.com/books?id=rUsUPZbFHK8C&pg=PA141|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Wind erosion is of two primary varieties: ''[[Aeolian_processes#Wind_erosion|deflation]]'', where the wind picks up and carries away loose particles; and ''[[Abrasion_(geology)|abrasion]]'', where surfaces are worn down as they are struck by airborne particles carried by wind. Deflation is divided into three categories: (1) ''[[Downhill_creep|surface creep]]'', where larger, heavier particles slide or roll along the ground; (2) ''[[Saltation_(geology)|saltation]]'', where particles are lifted a short height into the air, and bounce and saltate across the surface of the soil; and (3) ''[[Suspension_(chemistry)|suspension]]'', where very small and light particles are lifted into the air by the wind, and are often carried for long distances. Saltation is responsible for the majority (50–70%) of wind erosion, followed by suspension (30–40%), and then surface creep (5–25%).
<ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Wind erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|pages=56–57|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA57|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608092637/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA57|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|author=Balba, A. Monem|chapter=Desertification: Wind erosion|title=Management of Problem Soils in Arid Ecosystems|publisher=CRC Press|year=1995|isbn=978-0-87371-811-0|page=214|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uS62XNzDZDsC&pg=PA214|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801114426/https://books.google.com/books?id=uS62XNzDZDsC&pg=PA214|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在乾旱地區和乾旱時期，風蝕嚴重得多。例如，在[[北美大平原|北美大平原]]中，估計由於風蝕造成的土壤損失在乾旱年可能比在濕年高達6100倍。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Wiggs, Giles F.S.|chapter=Geomorphological hazards in drylands|editor=Thomas, David S.G.|title=Arid Zone Geomorphology: Process, Form and Change in Drylands|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2011|isbn=978-0-470-71076-0|page=588|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=swz4rh4KaLYC&pg=PA588|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801032908/https://books.google.com/books?id=swz4rh4KaLYC&pg=PA588|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 崩壞作用 ===
[[File:NegevWadi2009.JPG|thumb]]旱谷，顯示重力崩壞作用在運動。]]

'''[[崩壞作用|崩壞作用]]'''是岩石和沈積物在傾斜表面上的向下和向外運動， 主要是[[重力|重力]]慣性。<ref>{{cite book|author=Van Beek, Rens|chapter=Hillside processes: mass wasting, slope stability, and erosion|editor=Norris, Joanne E.|display-editors=etal|title=Slope Stability and Erosion Control: Ecotechnological Solutions|publisher=Springer|year=2008|isbn=978-1-4020-6675-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YWPcffxM_A0C&pg=PA17|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801115244/https://books.google.com/books?id=YWPcffxM_A0C&pg=PA17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Gray, Donald H.|author2=Sotir, Robbin B.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Surficial erosion and mass movement|title=Biotechnical and Soil Bioengineering Slope Stabilization: A Practical Guide for Erosion Control|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=1996|isbn=978-0-471-04978-4|page=20|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kCbp6IvFHrAC&pg=20|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801124446/https://books.google.com/books?id=kCbp6IvFHrAC&pg=20|dead-url=no}}</ref>

大量運動是侵蝕過程的重要部分，並且通常是山區中風化材料的分解和運輸的第一階段。<ref>{{cite book|author=Nichols, Gary|title=Sedimentology and Stratigraphy|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2009|isbn=978-1-4051-9379-5|page=93|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zl4L7WqXvogC&pg=PA93|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607063638/https://books.google.com/books?id=zl4L7WqXvogC&pg=PA93|dead-url=no}}</ref>它將材料從較高的高度移動到較低的高度，其中其它侵蝕劑例如水流和[[冰川|冰川]]然後可以拾取材料並將其移動到甚至更低的高度。質量運動過程總是在所有斜坡上連續發生；一些質量運動過程的行為非常緩慢；其他的發生非常突然，經常帶來災難性的後果。岩石或沉積物的任何可察覺的下坡運動通常被稱為[[滑坡|滑坡]]。然而，滑坡可以以更詳細的方式分類，反映了運動發生的機制和運動發生的速度。這種活動的非常緩慢形式的可見的地形表現之一是[[岩屑堆|岩屑堆]]。

[[坍落|坍落]]發生在陡峭的山坡上，沿著明顯的斷裂帶發生，經常發生在像[[黏土|黏土]]這樣的材料中，一旦釋放，它們可能很快下滑。在某些情況下，坍落度是由斜坡下的水使其變弱造成的。在許多情況下，是由[[公路|公路]]的不良工程造成的。

== 影響土壤侵蝕的因素 ==

=== 氣候 ===
降雨量的數量和強度是控制水土壤侵蝕的主要氣候因素。如果強降雨發生在土壤表面沒有被[[植被|植被]]良好保護的時間或地點，則這種關係特別強烈。這可能是在農業活動離開土壤的時期，或在[[半乾旱氣候|半乾旱氣候]]地區，其中植被是自然稀少的。風侵蝕需要強風，特別是在乾旱時期，當植被稀疏和土壤乾燥時（因此更易受侵蝕）。其他氣候因素，如平均溫度和溫度範圍，也可能影響侵蝕，通過它們對植被和土壤性質的影響。一般來說，由於類似的植被和生態系統，具有更多降水（特別是高強度降雨），更多風力或更多風暴的區域預計會有更多的侵蝕。

在世界的一些地區（例如美國中西部），降雨強度是侵蝕性的主要決定因素，較高強度的降雨通常導致水的更多的土壤侵蝕。[[降雨|降雨]]的大小和速度也是一個重要因素。較大和較高速度的雨滴具有較大的[動能]，因此它們的撞擊將使土壤顆粒的距離大於較小的，較慢移動的雨滴。<ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Water erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|pages=29–31|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA29|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610024009/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA29|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在西歐地區，徑流和侵蝕是由層狀降雨相對較低的強度落在先前飽和的土壤上造成的。在這種情況下，降水量而不是強度是決定水土壤侵蝕嚴重程度的主要因素。<ref>Boardman, John & Poesen, Jean. Soil Erosion in Europe. John Wiley & Sons. ISBN 978-0-470-85911-7</ref>

=== 土壤結構和組成 ===
[[File:Dead_Sea_Coastal_Erosion_March_2012.JPG|thumb]]（以色列）的侵蝕溝沉積在西南岸。 這個溝壑是在不到一年的時間內洪水中挖掘出來的。]]

土壤的組成，水分和壓實都是決定降雨侵蝕性的主要因素。含有更多[[粘土|粘土]]的沉積物比那些具有沙子或淤泥的沉積物更易於侵蝕，因為粘土有助於將污垢顆粒粘結在一起。<ref>{{cite book|author=Mirsal, Ibrahim A.|chapter=Soil degradation|title=Soil Pollution: Origin, Monitoring & Remediation|publisher=Springer|year=2008|isbn=978-3-540-70775-2|page=100|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Lr5bMTxom0IC&pg=PA100|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608092635/https://books.google.com/books?id=Lr5bMTxom0IC&pg=PA100|dead-url=no}}</ref>含有高含量有機材料的土壤通常更耐侵蝕，因為有機材料凝結土壤膠體並產生更強的，更穩定的土壤結構。<ref name="Blanco-2010-p29" />在沉澱之前存在於土壤中的水的量也起重要作用，因為它對可以被土壤吸收的水的量設置限制（並且因此防止其作為侵蝕性徑流在表面上流動）。濕的、飽和的土壤將不能吸收盡可能多的雨水，導致更高水平的表面徑流，因此對於給定體積的降雨具有更高的侵蝕性。<ref name="Blanco-2010-p29" /><ref>{{cite book|author=Torri, D.|chapter=Slope, aspect and surface storage|editor=Agassi, Menachem|title=Soil Erosion, Conservation, and Rehabilitation|publisher=CRC Press|year=1996|isbn=978-0-8247-8984-8|page=95|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-AqdSMDSUIgC&pg=PA95|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605183350/https://books.google.com/books?id=-AqdSMDSUIgC&pg=PA95|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[土壤壓實|土壤壓實]]也影響土壤對水的滲透性，因此也影響作為徑流流失的水量。 更加緊密的土壤將具有比較少壓實的土壤更大量的表面徑流。<ref name="Blanco-2010-p29">{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Water erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|page=29|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA29|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610024009/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA29|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 植被 ===
植被作為大氣和土壤之間的界面。它增加雨水滲透到土壤中，從而減少徑流。它保護土壤免受風，這導致風侵蝕減少，以及微氣候的有利變化。植物的根部將土壤結合在一起，並與其他根交織，形成更不易受水和風蝕的影響的更加固體的物質。植被的去除增加了表面侵蝕的速率。<ref>{{cite book|author=Styczen, M.E.|author2=Morgan, R.P.C.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Engineering properties of vegetation|editor=Morgan, R.P.C.|editor2=Rickson, R. Jane|title=Slope Stabilization and Erosion Control: A Bioengineering Approach|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=1995|isbn=978-0-419-15630-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3jXg9pyfikQC&pg=4|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085350/https://books.google.com/books?id=3jXg9pyfikQC&pg=4|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 地形 ===
土地的地形決定[[地表徑流|地表徑流]]將流動的速度，這反過來確定徑流的侵蝕性。更長、更陡的坡度（特別是沒有足夠植被覆蓋的那些）在大雨期間更容易受到非常高的侵蝕速率，比較短、不太陡的坡度、陡峭的地形也更容易發生泥石流。<ref>{{cite book|author=Whisenant, Steve G.|chapter=Terrestrial systems|editor=Perrow Michael R.|editor2=Davy, Anthony J.|title=Handbook of Ecological Restoration: Principles of Restoration|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2008|isbn=978-0-521-04983-2|page=89|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=moJHjZ9qW_8C&pg=PA89|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801085032/https://books.google.com/books?id=moJHjZ9qW_8C&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Water erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|pages=28–30|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA28|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611074018/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA28|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Wainwright, John|author2=Brazier, Richard E.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Slope systems|editor=Thomas, David S.G.|title=Arid Zone Geomorphology: Process, Form and Change in Drylands|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2011|isbn=978-0-470-71076-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=swz4rh4KaLYC&pg=PA209|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801101344/https://books.google.com/books?id=swz4rh4KaLYC&pg=PA209|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 增加水土流失的人類活動 ==

=== 慣習農業 ===
[[File:Soil_erosion_at_Hill_Farm_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1287527.jpg|thumb]]
[[慣習農業|慣習農業]]是全球侵蝕速度增加的最大因素。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Committee on 21st Century Systems Agriculture|title=Toward Sustainable Agricultural Systems in the 21st Century|publisher=National Academies Press|year=2010|isbn=978-0-309-14896-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wdm4qMW1azgC&pg=PT88|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820010411/https://books.google.com/books?id=wdm4qMW1azgC&pg=PT88|dead-url=no}}</ref>農田的[[耕地|耕地]]將土壤分解成更細的顆粒，是主要因素之一。由於機械化的農業設備允許[[深耕|深耕]]，這嚴重增加了可通過水蝕進行運輸的土壤的數量，這個問題在現代被加劇了。其他包括[[單一種植|單一種植]]，在陡坡上耕作，[[農藥|農藥]]和[[化肥|化肥]]的使用（其殺死將土壤粘在一起的生物）、排種以及[[表面灌溉|表面灌溉]]。<ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Tillage erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA109|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820011001/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA109|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Lobb, D.A.|chapter=Soil movement by tillage and other agricultural activities|editor=Jorgenson, Sven E.|title=Applications in Ecological Engineering|publisher=Academic Press|year=2009|isbn=978-0-444-53448-4|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aRKO6ZazC8UC&pg=PA247|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818222441/https://books.google.com/books?id=aRKO6ZazC8UC&pg=PA247|dead-url=no}}</ref>由於土壤侵蝕事件的大小選擇性性質，可能產生關於限定土壤養分損失的複雜的總體情況。例如，在較細的侵蝕部分中，[[磷|磷]]的損失相對於整個土壤更大。<ref>{{cite journal |title=Bioavailable phosphorus in fine-sized sediments transported from agricultural fields |author= Poirier, S.-C. |author2=Whalen, J.K. |author3=Michaud, A.R. |year= 2012|volume=76|issue=1|pages=258–267|doi= 10.2136/sssaj2010.0441|journal= Soil Science Society of America Journal }}</ref>推斷這一證據以預測接收水生系統中的後續行為，原因是與更粗的級分相比，更容易運輸的材料可以支持更低的溶液P濃度。<ref>{{cite journal |title= Phosphorus loss in overfertilized soils: The selective P partitioning and redistribution between particle size separates |author= Scalenghe, R. |author2= Edwards, A.C. |author3= Barberis, E. |last-author-amp= yes|year= 2007|volume=27|issue=11|pages=72–80|doi= 10.1016/j.eja.2007.02.002|journal= European Journal of Agronomy}}</ref>耕地還通過使土壤脫水並將其分解成可被風拾取的較小顆粒來增加風蝕速率。<ref>{{cite book|author=Whitford, Walter G.|chapter=Wind and water processes|title=Ecology of Desert Systems|publisher=Academic Press|year=2002|isbn=978-0-12-747261-4|page=65|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OZ4hZbXS8IcC&pg=PA65|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608081300/https://books.google.com/books?id=OZ4hZbXS8IcC&pg=PA65|dead-url=no}}</ref>重[[放牧|放牧]]減少植被覆蓋並導致嚴重的土壤壓實，這兩者都增加腐蝕速率。<ref>{{cite book|author=Imeson, Anton|chapter=Human impact on degradation processes|title=Desertification, Land Degradation and Sustainability|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2012|isbn=978-1-119-97776-6|page=165|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BjJQY-i7kNsC&pg=PA165|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609071002/https://books.google.com/books?id=BjJQY-i7kNsC&pg=PA165|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 砍伐森林 ===
[[File:BURNED_CLEAR-CUT_AREA_OF_OLYMPIC_NATIONAL_TIMBERLAND_WASHINGTON._NEAR_OLYMPIC_NATIONAL_PARK_-_NARA_-_555088.tif|thumb]]和營養豐富[[表土|表土]]的損失。]]

在不受干擾的[[森林|森林]]中，礦物土被一層覆蓋森林地面的[[廢棄物|廢棄物]]和[[腐殖質|腐殖質]]保護。這兩個層在土壤上形成吸收雨滴衝擊的保護墊。並允許[[雨水|雨水]]減緩[[滲出|滲出]]進入下面的土壤，而不是作為[[地表徑流|地表徑流]]在表面上流動。<ref name="Sands-2005-pp74-75">{{cite book|author=Sands, Roger|chapter=The environmental value of forests|title=Forestry in a Global Context|publisher=CABI|year=2005|isbn=978-0-85199-089-7|pages=74–75|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UO1DAI60IQEC&pg=PA74|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610060537/https://books.google.com/books?id=UO1DAI60IQEC&pg=PA74|dead-url=no}}</ref>樹和植物的根<ref>The [[Mycelium|mycelia]] of forest [[Fungus|fungi]] also play a major role in binding soil particles together.</ref>保持土壤顆粒，防止它們被沖走。<ref name="Sands-2005-pp74-75" />植物覆蓋物用於降低在撞擊地面之前撞擊葉片和莖的雨滴的速度，從而減少它們的[動能]。<ref name="Goudie-2000-p188" />然而，它是森林地板，多于冠層，防止表面侵蝕。 在{{convert|8|m|ft|abbr=off}}中達到雨滴的終點速度。因為森林簷篷通常高於這個，雨滴通常可以重獲終點速度，即使在擊中了冠層。然而，完整的森林地板，其各層葉片和有機物質，仍然能夠吸收降雨的影響。<ref name="Goudie-2000-p188">{{Cite book|author=Goudie, Andrew|chapter=The human impact on the soil|title=The Human Impact on the Natural Environment|publisher=MIT Press|year=2000|isbn=978-0-262-57138-8|page=188|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=r8l-DMj3XTgC&pg=PA188|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610024011/https://books.google.com/books?id=r8l-DMj3XTgC&pg=PA188|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Stuart, Gordon W.|author2=Edwards, Pamela J.|last-author-amp=yes|title=Concepts about forests and water|work=Northern Journal of Applied Forestry|volume=23|issue=1|year=2006|url=http://treesearch.fs.fed.us/pubs/14744|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2017-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701142057/https://www.treesearch.fs.fed.us/pubs/14744|dead-url=no}}</ref>

砍伐森林通過從土壤表面除去腐殖質和凋落物層，去除了將土壤結合在一起的植被覆蓋物而引起[[礦物|礦物]] [[土壤壓實|土壤壓實]]。一旦[[火災|火災]]或伐木移除了樹木，入侵率變高，侵蝕低到森林地板保持完好的程度。嚴重的如果緊接著暴雨可能導致顯著的進一步[[侵蝕|侵蝕]]。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Goudie, Andrew|chapter=The human impact on the soil|title=The Human Impact on the Natural Environment|publisher=MIT Press|year=2000|isbn=978-0-262-57138-8|pages=196–197|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=r8l-DMj3XTgC&pg=PA196|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190602085455/https://books.google.com/books?id=r8l-DMj3XTgC&pg=PA196|dead-url=no}}</ref>

全球範圍內2006年侵蝕性土壤流失的最大貢獻者之一是[[熱帶|熱帶]][[森林|森林]]的砍伐和焚燒。在地球的一些地區，一個國家的整個部門都沒有生產效率。例如，在[[馬達加斯加|馬達加斯加]]高中心[[高原|高原]]上，佔該國土地面積的大約百分之十，幾乎整個景觀都是[[植被|植被]]光禿的，溝壑腐蝕的溝通常超過{{convert|50|m|ft}}深和{{convert|1|km|mi|abbr=off|1}}寬。

=== 道路和城市化 ===
[[城市化|城市化]]對侵蝕過程有重大影響 - 首先是剝蝕植被覆蓋土地，改變排水模式，在施工期間壓實土壤; 接下來通過在瀝青或混凝土的不可滲透層中覆蓋土地，增加表面徑流的量並增加地面風速。<ref>{{cite book|author=Nîr, Dov|title=Man, a Geomorphological Agent: An Introduction to Anthropic Geomorphology|publisher=Springer|year=1983|isbn=978-90-277-1401-5|pages=121–122|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3HSCQvZ7U2kC&pg=PA121|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610060546/https://books.google.com/books?id=3HSCQvZ7U2kC&pg=PA121|dead-url=no}}</ref>從城市地區（特別是道路）徑流中攜帶的大部分沉積物被燃料，油和其他化學品高度污染。<ref>{{cite book|author=Randhir, Timothy O.|title=Watershed Management: Issues and Approaches|publisher=IWA Publishing|year=2007|isbn=978-1-84339-109-8|page=56|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PNBlSPdu0JAC&pg=PA56|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608143511/https://books.google.com/books?id=PNBlSPdu0JAC&pg=PA56|dead-url=no}}</ref>這種增加的徑流，除了侵蝕和降解流經的土地，還通過改變流經它們的水的體積和速率，並且對它們進行化學污染的沉積，對周圍流域造成嚴重破壞。通過當地水道的增加的水流也導致土地侵蝕速度的大幅增加。<ref>{{cite book|author=James, William|chapter=Channel and habitat change downstream of urbanization|editor=Herricks, Edwin E.|editor2=Jenkins, Jackie R.|title=Stormwater Runoff and Receiving Systems: Impact, Monitoring, and Assessment|publisher=CRC Press|year=1995|isbn=978-1-56670-159-4|page=105|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=X0xt9HZbyToC&pg=PA105|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612163027/https://books.google.com/books?id=X0xt9HZbyToC&pg=PA105|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 氣候變化 ===
