[[File:Rano_Raraku_quarry.jpg|thumb]]由於[[砍伐森林|砍伐森林]]和不可持續的農業做法而遭受嚴重侵蝕。 由此造成的表土損失最終導致生態崩潰，造成群島[[飢餓|飢餓]]和復活節島文明的完全瓦解。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Dangerfield, Whitney|title=The Mystery of Easter Island|work=Smithsonian Magazine|date=April 1, 2007|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/people-places/The_Mystery_of_Easter_Island.html|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2009-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090507210658/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/people-places/The_Mystery_of_Easter_Island.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Montgomery, David|chapter=Islands in time|title=Dirt: The Erosion of Civilizations|publisher=University of California Press|date=October 2, 2008|edition=1st|isbn=978-0-520-25806-8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HSu8r15-nnoC&pg=PA217|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612025638/https://books.google.com/books?id=HSu8r15-nnoC&pg=PA217|dead-url=no}}</ref>]]

由於其生態效應的嚴重性及其發生的規模，侵蝕是我們今天面臨的最重要的全球環境問題之一。<ref name="toy-2002-p1">{{cite book|author=Toy, Terrence J.|title=Soil Erosion: Processes, Prediction, Measurement, and Control|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2002|isbn=978-0-471-38369-7|page=1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7YBaKZ-28j0C&pg=PA1|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605230833/https://books.google.com/books?id=7YBaKZ-28j0C&pg=PA1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 土地退化 ===
水和風侵蝕現在是[[土地退化|土地退化]]的兩個主要原因；結合起來，他們負責84％的退化面積。<ref name="Springer"/>

每年，大約750億噸土壤從土地侵蝕這是自然速度的13至40倍的速度。<ref>{{cite book|author=Zuazo, Victor H.D.|author2=Pleguezuelo, Carmen R.R.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Soil-erosion and runoff prevention by plant covers: a review|editor=Lichtfouse, Eric|display-editors=etal|title=Sustainable agriculture|publisher=Springer|year=2009|isbn=978-90-481-2665-1|page=785|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7cP-2jIIO2wC&pg=PA785|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607165036/https://books.google.com/books?id=7cP-2jIIO2wC&pg=PA785|dead-url=no}}</ref>世界上約40％的農地嚴重退化。<ref>{{cite news|author=Sample, Ian|title=Global food crisis looms as climate change and population growth strip fertile land|work=The Guardian|date=August 30, 2007|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2007/aug/31/climatechange.food|accessdate=2017-01-30|archive-date=2016-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160429094959/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2007/aug/31/climatechange.food|dead-url=no}}</ref>根據[[聯合國|聯合國]]，每年因為[[乾旱|乾旱]]，[[砍伐森林|砍伐森林]]和[[氣候變化|氣候變化]]，烏克蘭面積肥沃的土地面積減少。<ref>{{cite news|author=Smith, Kate|author2=Edwards, Rob|last-author-amp=yes|title=2008: The year of global food crisis|work=The Herald (Scotland)|date=March 8, 2008|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/2008-the-year-of-global-food-crisis-1.828546|accessdate=2017-01-30|archive-date=2013-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130411220739/http://www.heraldscotland.com/2008-the-year-of-global-food-crisis-1.828546|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[非洲|非洲]]，根據[[聯合國大學|聯合國大學]]設在加納的自然研究所，如果當前土壤退化趨勢繼續下去，該大陸可能只能在2025年前為其人口提供25％非洲資源。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.mongabay.com/2006/1214-unu.html |title=Africa may be able to feed only 25% of its population by 2025 |access-date=2017-01-30 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/10702/20110227154823/http://news.mongabay.com/2006/1214-unu.html |archive-date=2011-02-27 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

由於侵蝕造成的土壤肥力損失是進一步的問題，因為反應通常是施用化肥，這導致進一步的水和土壤污染，而不是允許土地再生。<ref>{{cite book|author=Potter, Kenneth W.|chapter=Impacts of agriculture on aquatic ecosystems in the humid United States|editor=DeFries, Ruth S.|display-editors=etal|title=Ecosystems And Land Use Change|publisher=American Geophysical Union|year=2004|isbn=978-0-87590-418-4|page=34|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CVN5X57pjnAC&pg=PA34|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2014-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329035322/http://books.google.com/books?id=CVN5X57pjnAC&pg=PA34|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 水生生態系統的沉積 ===
由於過量沉積物流入世界水道的影響，土壤侵蝕（特別是來自農業活動）被認為是擴散[[水污染|水污染]]的全球主要原因。沉積物本身作為污染物，以及作為其他污染物的載體，如附著的農藥分子或重金屬。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Da Cunha, L.V.|chapter=Sustainable development of water resources|editor=Bau, João|title=Integrated Approaches to Water Pollution Problems: Proceedings of the International Symposium (SISIPPA) (Lisbon, Portugal 19–23 June 1989)|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=1991|isbn=978-1-85166-659-1|pages=12–13|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=79ztZNhaNvMC&pg=PA12|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609012203/https://books.google.com/books?id=79ztZNhaNvMC&pg=PA12|dead-url=no}}</ref>

增加沉積物對水生生態系統的影響可能是災難性的。泥沙可以窒息魚的產卵床，通過填充在流床上的礫石之間的空間。它還減少了它們的食物供應，並且當沉積物進入其[[鰓|鰓]]時，引起它們的主要呼吸問題。水生植物和藻類生物的[[生物多樣性|生物多樣性]]減少，無脊椎動物也無法生存和繁殖。雖然沉積事件本身可能相對短暫，但由大量死亡引起的生態破壞通常在未來持續很長時間。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Merrington, Graham|chapter=Soil erosion|title=Agricultural Pollution: Environmental Problems and Practical Solutions|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=2002|isbn=978-0-419-21390-1|pages=77–78|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ITFYBiQ_-VAC&pg=PA77|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610062642/https://books.google.com/books?id=ITFYBiQ_-VAC&pg=PA77|dead-url=no}}</ref>

世界上最嚴重和長期存在的水蝕問題之一是在[[中華人民共和國|中華人民共和國]]，在[黃河]的中層和[長江]的上游。[[黃河|黃河]]每年超過16億噸的沉積物流入海洋。[[沉積物|沉積物]]主要來自西北[[黃土高原|黃土高原]]區域的水土流失。

=== 空氣粉塵污染 ===
在土壤風蝕期間拾取的土壤顆粒是[[空氣污染|空氣污染]]的主要來源，空氣中顆粒 -'''灰塵'''的形式。這些空氣中的土壤顆粒通常被有毒化學品如農藥或石油燃料污染，當他們以後著陸或被吸入或攝入時構成生態和公共健康危害。<ref>{{cite book|author=Majewski, Michael S.|author2=Capel, Paul D.|last-author-amp=yes|title=Pesticides in the Atmosphere: Distribution, Trends, and Governing Factors|publisher=CRC Press|year=1996|isbn=978-1-57504-004-2|page=121|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T9pRfLqXajQC&pg=PA121|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610092909/https://books.google.com/books?id=T9pRfLqXajQC&pg=PA121|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Science Daily 1999-07-14">{{cite web|author=Science Daily|date=1999-07-14|url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/1999/07/990714073433.htm|title=African Dust Called A Major Factor Affecting Southeast U.S. Air Quality|accessdate=2007-06-10|archive-date=2017-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707072700/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/1999/07/990714073433.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Nowell, Lisa H.|title=Pesticides in Stream Sediment and Aquatic Biota: Distribution, Trends, and Governing Factors|publisher=CRC Press|year=1999|isbn=978-1-56670-469-4|page=199|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UzpDTEO3ZVcC&pg=PA199|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609192643/https://books.google.com/books?id=UzpDTEO3ZVcC&pg=PA199|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Shao, Yaping|chapter=Wind-erosion and wind-erosion research|title=Physics and Modelling of Wind Erosion|publisher=Springer|year=2008|isbn=978-1-4020-8894-0|page=3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XSwwVeraxjcC&pg=PA3|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612235711/https://books.google.com/books?id=XSwwVeraxjcC&pg=PA3|dead-url=no}}</ref>

灰塵從侵蝕起作用以抑制降雨並將[[天空|天空]]顏色從藍色改變為白色，這導致紅色日落的增加。塵埃事件與加勒比和佛羅里達州主要自1970年代以來[[珊瑚礁|珊瑚礁]]的健康下降有關。<ref>{{cite web|author=U. S. Geological Survey|author-link=U. S. Geological Survey|year=2006|url=http://coastal.er.usgs.gov/african_dust/|title=Coral Mortality and African Dust|accessdate=2007-06-10|archive-date=2012-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502091350/http://coastal.er.usgs.gov/african_dust/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>類似的塵埃起源於[[戈壁沙漠|戈壁沙漠]]，它與污染物結合，在下風向或東向傳播大距離進入北美。<ref name="Gobi">{{cite web |author=James K. B. Bishop |author2=Russ E. Davis |author3=Jeffrey T. Sherman |last-author-amp=yes |year=2002 |url=http://www-ocean.lbl.gov/people/bishop/bishoppubs/paparobots.html |title=Robotic Observations of Dust Storm Enhancement of Carbon Biomass in the North Pacific |work=Science 298 |pages=817–821 |accessdate=2009-06-20 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5uLajGMw8?url=http://www-ocean.lbl.gov/people/bishop/bishoppubs/paparobots.html |archivedate=2010-11-19 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

== 監測、測量和模擬水土流失 ==
[[File:Landscape_Madagascar_06.jpg|thumb]]是一種古老的技術，可以顯著減慢水耕侵蝕的速度。]]

侵蝕過程的監測和建模可以幫助人們更好地理解土壤侵蝕的原因，對侵蝕進行預測在一系列可能條件下的情景規劃，併計劃然而，侵蝕過程的複雜性和必須考慮的科學學科的數量來理解和建模它們（例如[[氣候學|氣候學]]、[[水文學|水文學]]、[[地質學|地質學]]、[[水文學|水文學]]、[[土壤科學|土壤科學]]、[[農業|農業]]、[[化學|化學]]、[[物理|物理]]等）使準確的建模具有挑戰性。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Evans|first1=R|title=Assessment and monitoring of accelerated water erosion of cultivated land – when will reality be acknowledged?|journal=Soil Use and Management|date=2012|volume=29|issue=1|pages=105–118|doi=10.1111/sum.12010|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/sum.12010/full|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2017-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430063602/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/sum.12010/full|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Modeling water and wind erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA81|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2014-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329023953/http://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA81|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>See also: {{cite book|author=Shai, Yaping|title=Physics and Modelling of Wind Erosion|publisher=Springer|year=2008|isbn=978-1-4020-8894-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XSwwVeraxjcC|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610062640/https://books.google.com/books?id=XSwwVeraxjcC|dead-url=no}} and {{cite book|author1=Harmon, Russell S.|author2=Doe, William W.|lastauthoramp=yes|title=Landscape Erosion and Evolution Modeling|publisher=Springer|year=2001|isbn=978-0-306-46718-9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RltaPlIHlrAC|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608205951/https://books.google.com/books?id=RltaPlIHlrAC|dead-url=no}}</ref> 侵蝕模型也是非線性的，這使得它們難以在數字上工作，並且使得難以或不可能按照通過對較小的圖採樣所收集的數據來對大面積進行預測。<ref>{{cite book|author=Brazier, R.E.|chapter=Scaling soil erosion models in space and time|editor=Morgan, Royston P.C.|editor2=Nearing, Mark|title=Handbook of Erosion Modelling|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2011|isbn=978-1-4051-9010-7|page=100|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pSO4X3XbhJIC&pg=PA100|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611145400/https://books.google.com/books?id=pSO4X3XbhJIC&pg=PA100|dead-url=no}}</ref>

最常用的預測水土流失土壤流失的模型是「[[通用土壤流失公式|通用土壤流失公式]]」（USLE）。這是在20世紀60年代和70年代開發的。它估計一塊地塊面積上的年平均土壤流失量（A）<ref>{{cite book|author=Ward, Andrew D.|author2=Trimble, Stanley W.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Soil conservation and sediment budgets|title=Environmental Hydrology|publisher=CRC Press|year=2004|isbn=978-1-56670-616-2|page=259|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yANwmTjf588C&pg=PA259|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611053215/https://books.google.com/books?id=yANwmTjf588C&pg=PA259|dead-url=no}}</ref>：
: ''A = RKLSCP''
其中R是降雨沖蝕指數<ref>{{cite journal|author=Panagos, P.|author2=Ballabio, C.|author3=Borrelli, P.|author4=Meusburger, K.|author5=Klik, A.|author6=Rousseva, S.|author7=Tadic, M.P.|author8=Michaelides, S.|author9=Hrabalíková, M.|author10=Olsen, P.|author11=Aalto, J.|author12=Lakatos, M.|author13=Rymszewicz, A.|author14=Dumitrescu, A.|author15=Beguería, S.|author16=Alewell, C.|title=Rainfall Erosivity in Europe|journal=Sci Total Environ.|year=2015|DOI=10.1016/j.scitotenv.2015.01.008|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S004896971500011X|volume=511|pages=801–814|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217133626/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S004896971500011X|dead-url=no}}</ref>，K是土壤沖蝕指數，L和S表示地形因子<ref>{{cite news|author=Panagos, P.|author2=Borrelli, P.|author3=Meusburger|title=A New European Slope Length and Steepness Factor (LS-Factor) for Modeling Soil Erosion by Water|publisher=Geosciences, MDPI|year=2015|pages=117–126|DOI=10.3390/geosciences5020117|url=http://www.mdpi.com/2076-3263/5/2/117|accessdate=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-07-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190715105100/https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3263/5/2/117|dead-url=no}}</ref>（其中L為坡長因子，S為坡度因子），C是覆蓋與管理因子，P則是水土保持處理因子。

儘管USLE的'''plot-scale spatial focus'''，該模型經常被用於估計更大面積上的土壤侵蝕，例如[[集水區|集水區]]或甚至整個[[陸地|陸地]]。例如：修正版通用土壤流失公式（Revised Universal Soil Loss Equation，RUSLE）最近被用於量化整個歐洲的土壤侵蝕<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://esdac.jrc.ec.europa.eu/content/soil-erosion-water-rusle2015 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2017-01-30 |archive-date=2021-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112100200/https://esdac.jrc.ec.europa.eu/content/soil-erosion-water-rusle2015 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這是科學上有爭議的，有幾個原因。一個主要問題是，USLE不能模擬溝槽侵蝕，因此在任何基於USLE的侵蝕評估中忽略來自溝槽的侵蝕。然而，溝渠侵蝕可能是耕地和牧草土地總侵蝕的很大比例（10-80％）。<ref>{{cite book|author=Boardman, J.|author2=Poesen, J.|chapter=Soil erosion in Europe: major processes, causes and consequences|title=Soil Erosion in Europe|publisher=Wiley, Chichester|year=2006|pages=479–487|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/book/10.1002/0470859202|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2018-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203060833/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/book/10.1002/0470859202|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在引入USLE後的50年中，已經開發了許多其它土壤侵蝕模型。<ref>{{cite book|author=Jetten, V.|author2=Favis-Mortlock, D.|chapter=Modelling soil erosion in Europe|title=Soil Erosion in Europe|publisher=Wiley, Chichester|year=2006|pages=695–716|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/book/10.1002/0470859202|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2018-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203060833/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/book/10.1002/0470859202|dead-url=no}}</ref>但是由於土壤侵蝕及其構成過程的複雜性，當驗證時，即當將模型預測與侵蝕的現實測量進行比較時，所有侵蝕模型都可能產生不令人滿意的結果。<ref>{{cite book|author=Favis-Mortlock, D.|chapter=Validation of field-scale soil erosion models using common datasets|title=Modelling Soil Erosion by Water|publisher=Springer-Verlag NATO-ARS Series 1–55, Berlin|year=1998|pages=89–128|url=http://www.springer.com/us/book/9783642637872|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2020-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927052526/https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783642637872|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Jetten, V.|author2=De Roo, A.P.J.|author3=Favis-Mortlock, D.T.|title=Evaluation of field-scale and catchment scale soil erosion models|year=1999|journal=Catena|volume=37|pages=521–541|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/03418162/37/3-4|doi=10.1016/s0341-8162(99)00037-5|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2016-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160725125410/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/03418162/37/3-4|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 預防和治理 ==
[[File:Windbreak_near_New_Alyth_-_geograph.org.uk_-_687555.jpg|thumb]]（一排樹）種植在一個農田旁邊，作為抵抗強風的盾牌。 這降低了風蝕的影響，並提供了許多其他好處。]]

防止侵蝕的最有效的已知方法是增加土地上的植被覆蓋，這有助於防止風和水的侵蝕。<ref>{{cite book|author=Connor, David J.|title=Crop Ecology: Productivity and Management in Agricultural Systems|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2011|isbn=978-0-521-74403-4|page=351|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O2eh7vyvuscC&pg=PA351|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607195648/https://books.google.com/books?id=O2eh7vyvuscC&pg=PA351|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[梯田|梯田]]是一種非常有效的侵蝕控製手段，它已經被世界各地的人們實踐了數千年。<ref>For an interesting archaeological/historical survey of terracing systems, see {{cite book|author=Treacy, John M.|author2=Denevan, William M.|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=The creation of cultivable land through terracing|editor=Miller, Naomi A.|title=The Archaeology of Garden and Field|publisher=University of Pennsylvania Press|year=1998|isbn=978-0-8122-1641-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MARsWXbqFCsC&pg=PA91|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605095755/https://books.google.com/books?id=MARsWXbqFCsC&pg=PA91|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[防風林|防風林]]（也稱為防護林）是沿著農田的邊緣種植的樹木和灌木，以遮蔽風場。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Forman, Richard T.T.|chapter=Windbreaks, hedgerows, and woodland corridors|title=Land Mosaics: The Ecology of Landscapes and Regions|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1995|isbn=978-0-521-47980-6|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sSRNU_5P5nwC&pg=PA177|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605230834/https://books.google.com/books?id=sSRNU_5P5nwC&pg=PA177|dead-url=no}}</ref>除了顯著減少風蝕外，防風林還提供許多其它益處，例如改善作物（其受到脫水和其他損害性風的影響），有利的鳥類物種的棲息地，<ref>{{cite book|author=Johnson, R.J.|chapter=Global perspectives on birds in agricultural landscapes|editor=Campbell, W. Bruce|editor2=Ortiz, Silvia Lopez|title=Integrating Agriculture, Conservation and Ecotourism: Examples from the Field|publisher=Springer|year=2011|isbn=978-94-007-1308-6|page=76|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=85KuKnayVMEC&pg=PA76|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612053252/https://books.google.com/books?id=85KuKnayVMEC&pg=PA76|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[固碳|固碳]]，<ref>{{cite book|author=Udawatta, Ranjith P.|author2=Shibu, Jose|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Carbon sequestration potential of agroforestry practices in temperate North America|editor=Kumar, B. Mohan|editor2=Nair, P.K.R.|title=Carbon Sequestration Potential of Agroforestry Systems: Opportunities and Challenges|publisher=Springer|year=2011|isbn=978-94-007-1629-2|pages=35–36|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oDzvVdD_dHwC&pg=PA35|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603135037/https://books.google.com/books?id=oDzvVdD_dHwC&pg=PA35|dead-url=no}}</ref>和美學改善農業景觀。<ref>{{cite book|author=Blanco, Humberto|author2=Lal, Rattan|last-author-amp=yes|chapter=Wind erosion|title=Principles of Soil Conservation and Management|publisher=Springer|year=2010|isbn=978-90-481-8529-0|page=69|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA69|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605182305/https://books.google.com/books?id=Wj3690PbDY0C&pg=PA69|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Nair, P.K.R.|title=An Introduction to Agroforestry|publisher=Springer|year=1993|isbn=978-0-7923-2135-4|pages=333–338|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CkVSeRpmIx8C&pg=PA333|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605230831/https://books.google.com/books?id=CkVSeRpmIx8C&pg=PA333|dead-url=no}}</ref>傳統的種植方法，如混合種植而不是單作和[[作物輪作|作物輪作]]也已顯示出顯著降低侵蝕速率。<ref>{{cite book|author=Lal, Rattan|title=Tillage Systems in the Tropics: Management Options and Sustainability Implications, Issue 71|publisher=Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations|year=1995|isbn=978-92-5-103776-8|pages=157–160|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Cxxj2VczLG0C&pg=PA157|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603200927/https://books.google.com/books?id=Cxxj2VczLG0C&pg=PA157|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>See also: {{cite book|author=Gajri, P.R.|title=Tillage for sustainable cropping|publisher=Psychology Press|year=2002|isbn=978-1-56022-903-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i_acg2gACb8C|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2014-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329033813/http://books.google.com/books?id=i_acg2gACb8C|dead-url=no}} and {{cite book|author=Uri, Noel D.|title=Conservation Tillage in United States Agriculture|publisher=Psychology Press|year=1999|isbn=978-1-56022-884-4|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2uPYFG3XLoEC|access-date=2017-01-30|archive-date=2019-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605134312/https://books.google.com/books?id=2uPYFG3XLoEC|dead-url=no}}</ref>作物殘留物在緩解侵蝕中起作用，因為它們減少了雨滴破壞土壤顆粒的影響。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://extension.psu.edu/plants/crops/soil-management/conservation-tillage/cover-crops-for-conservation-tillage-systems|title=Cover Crops for Conservation Tillage Methods|last=Curran|first=W.|date=2016|website=|publisher=Penn State University|access-date=December 1, 2016|archive-date=2017-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828044013/http://extension.psu.edu/plants/crops/soil-management/conservation-tillage/cover-crops-for-conservation-tillage-systems|dead-url=no}}</ref> 當生產馬鈴薯時，比種植穀物或油籽作物時侵蝕的可能性更大。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.mb.ca/agriculture/crops/production/potatoes-soil-management-on-potato-land.html|title=Soil Management on Potato Land|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|publisher=Government of Manitoba|access-date=December 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202170215/https://www.gov.mb.ca/agriculture/crops/production/potatoes-soil-management-on-potato-land.html|archive-date=2016-12-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 牧草具有纖維根系，其通過將植物錨定到土壤的頂層並覆蓋整個田地來幫助抵抗侵蝕，因為它是'''non-row crop'''。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://homeguides.sfgate.com/advantages-fibrous-root-taproot-systems-104165.html|title=The Advantages of the Fibrous Root & Taproot Systems|access-date=2016-12-01|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129164826/https://homeguides.sfgate.com/advantages-fibrous-root-taproot-systems-104165.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在熱帶沿海系統中，紅樹林的性質已被作為減少土壤侵蝕的潛在手段加以研究。 已知它們的複雜根結構有助於減少來自暴風雨和洪水沖擊的波浪損傷，同時結合和建造土壤。 這些根可以減緩水流，導致沉積物沉積和減少侵蝕率。 然而，為了保持沉積物平衡，需要存在充足的紅樹林寬度。<ref>Spalding M, McIvor A, Tonneijck FH, Tol S and van Eijk P (2014) Mangroves for coastal defence. Guidelines for coastal managers & policy makers. Published by Wetlands International and The Nature Conservancy. 42 p</ref>
